<DOCNO> AP890110-0064 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-01-10-89 0529EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Japan-Cars     01-10 0130</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Japan-Cars,0133</SECOND>
<HEAD>Japan's Auto Imports Hit Record 133,583</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Japan imported a record 133,583 cars in 1988, the
third straight year auto imports increased, the Japan Automobile
Importers Association announced today.
   Three West German carmakers _ Bavarian Motor Works, Volkswagen
and Mercedes-Benz _ were the most popular, the association said.
   The association credited intensifying competition and advertising
for the 35.5 percent increase in imports over 1987. It said 17,135
cars were imported in December, marking the 60th consecutive monthly
increase on a year-to-year basis.
   It said tax laws, due to take effect April 1, are expected to
lead to increased sales of larger import cars. The law abolishes the
23 percent tax for cars with engines over 2,000 cubic centimeters,
adding a 6 percent sales tax instead.
</TEXT>
