<HEAD>Sajak Premiere Beats `Tonight' in Big Cities</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-AP on TV-Sajak Show</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   It remains to be seen whether CBS' Pat Sajak can
beat NBC late-night king Johnny Carson, but the premiere of ``The
Pat Sajak Show'' did out-rate ``The Tonight Show'' with Jay Leno as
guest host Monday night.
   According to A.C. Nielsen Co. television ratings from the 17
biggest television markets, Sajak's 90-minute talk show had a rating
of 7.0 and a 25 share, to a 6.1 and 18 for the hour-long ``Tonight.''
   Sajak also was up against the first half of ``Late Night with
David Letterman'' and ABC's half-hour news show ``Nightline.''
Ratings for those shows were not immediately available.
   The rating is a percentage of total homes with televisions in the
markets surveyed. The share is a percentage of sets in use.
   Sajak and Carson won't go head-to-head until Wednesday night.
