Maas had shaken him violently because he was crying.
   She also was convicted of three counts of felony child abuse
related to David's death and injuries sustained by a 6-month-old boy
who suffered a bruised ear and a 7-month-old boy who suffered a
broken leg while in her care.
   A psychiatrist called by Ms. Maas's attorney had testified that
the baby sitter suffered a brain disorder that led to periodic bouts
of violent behavior similar to seizures.
