<UNK>`Inside Edition' Falters in Bid to Unseat `Current Affair'</UNK>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The syndicated show ``Inside Edition''
stumbled badly in its first attempt to challenge Fox's ``A Current
Affair,'' according to preliminary ratings announced Tuesday.
   Despite a $7 million promotion budget, the largest in syndicated
television history, ``Inside Edition'' drew an unspectacular rating
of 6.9 in 15 cities. One A.C. Nielsen Co. rating point is equivalent
to approximately 900,000 households with television.
   The show's producers have guaranteed a national rating of eight,
according to a report in the trade weekly Electronic Media.
   ``Inside Edition,'' a half-hour ``news'' show with host David
Frost, was beaten in both New York and Los Angeles by the Fox
Broadcasting Co.'s ``A Current Affair.'' ``Inside Edition'' gathered
a strong rating in Sacramento, topping ``A Current Affair'' there.
