<HEAD>Mayor Acknowledges `Character Failures'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KEWANEE, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mayor Emerit Lindbeck says he knows he has
some ``character failures.''
   His indictment in a vote-fraud case caused a stir in this
west-central Illinois community of 16,000 people. Then, he was
accused of slugging a man dressed as Santa Claus on Christmas Eve.
   ``If I've done anything wrong, I'm sorry. And I will change,''
Lindbeck vowed at the close of Monday's City Council meeting. ``I
want you to know I wouldn't do anything to harm this community in
which I was born and raised.''
