<SECOND>BC-Italy-Autos,0106</SECOND>
<HEAD>Italian Car Sales Top 2 Million in 1988</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TURIN, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic car sales rose 10 percent in 1988
over the previous year, a trade report released Tuesday said.
   The Italian Association of Auto Makers said that 2.184 million
cars were sold last year, compared with 1.976 million in 1987. Of
them, around 60 percent were from Italian companies, nearly
unchanged from the previous year, it said.
   Fiat, Italy's auto giant, held of a 44 percent market share,
while France's Renault was the best seller among foreign brands with
a market share of 7.1 percent, the report said.
