<FIRST>r f AM-Disney-Salary     01-10 0211</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Disney-Salary,0220</SECOND>
<HEAD>Disney Chairman Earned $40 Million in 1988</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BURBANK, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Walt Disney Co. Chairman Michael Eisner
earned $40.2 million in 1988, mainly in profits from a stock-option
plan, according to company proxy material.
   The disclosure Monday shows that Eisner remains one of the
nation's highest paid executives.
   Eisner realized a $32.6 million profit from the company stock
options program last year and a $6.8 million bonus in addition to
his $750,000 salary, the proxy statement said. Eisner's 1987 bonus
was $6 million.
   Disney also provides Eisner with $3 million in life insurance.
   The studio executive was given the option to purchase up to 2
million Disney shares at $14.54 per share when he joined the company
in 1984. The stock is currently trading above $65 a share.
   The proxy material disclosed that Eisner purchased 683,857 shares
of Disney stock last year. Of that total, he sold 330,390 for a
profit of $32.6 million. He still holds options to purchase an
additional 948,143 shares.
   Eisner now holds 353,467 Disney shares directly, or less than 1
percent of the outstanding shares. His wife and children hold an
additional 28,800 Disney shares.
   Under Eisner's leadership, Disney has enjoyed a string of hit
movies and increased revenues at its theme parks.
</TEXT>
