upcoming crop report from the Agriculture Department. Friday's
report will include final 1988 crop production figures, estimates
for 1989 planted acreage and new supply-demand statistics.
   At the close of trading, wheat was \ cent to 2 cents lower with
the contract for delivery in March at $4.46} a bushel; corn was 1
cent lower to \ cent higher with March at $2.89{ a bushel; oats were
{ cent lower to 1\ cents higher with March at $2.39 a bushel;
